---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';

const title = 'About IgnitionSim & Robert Pruitt';
const description = "I test the gear so you don't gamble on it. IgnitionSim is an independent, engineer-minded authority on sim hardware — honest verdicts, real compatibility, no affiliate fluff.";

const schema = [{
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'Person',
  name: site.author.name, jobTitle: site.author.role,
  description: site.author.bio, url: new URL('/about', site.url).href,
  worksFor: { '@type': 'Organization', name: site.name, url: site.url },
  sameAs: site.author.sameAs,
  knowsAbout: ['Sim racing hardware', 'Flight simulation hardware', 'Space sim controllers', 'Golf simulators', 'Direct drive wheelbases', 'HOTAS and HOSAS', 'Launch monitors'],
}];
---
<Base title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span>About</div>
    <section class="hero" style="text-align:left;padding:48px 0 20px">
      <div class="lbl lbl-accent">// {site.author.role}</div>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.2rem,5vw,3.4rem);max-width:18ch;margin:14px 0">I test the gear so you don't gamble on it.</h1>
      <p style="max-width:62ch;font-size:1.12rem">— {site.author.name}</p>
    </section>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>{site.name} exists because the simulation-hardware market is a maze. A wheelbase, a wheel, a set of pedals and a cockpit can total two or three thousand dollars — and half of them don't fit together. Quick-release standards clash. Ecosystems lock you in. Launch monitors need a room you might not have. Restocks vanish in minutes. Most "reviews" are a thin layer of marketing over an affiliate link.</p>

      <p>I'm {site.author.name}. {site.author.bio} I've spent two decades around engineering, robotics and machine-learning talent — which means I read a spec sheet the way other people read a menu, and I'm constitutionally incapable of recommending something just because it's popular.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-test">How we test and what we won't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>We test against reality, not press releases.</strong> Compatibility logic here reflects the actual quick-release, mount and torque standards manufacturers ship — encoded into the Rig Configurator so you can check a build before you buy it.</li>
        <li><strong>We'll tell you to skip something.</strong> An honest "this is overkill for you" or "buy the cheaper one" is worth more than any affiliate commission. If a product isn't right, we say so.</li>
        <li><strong>We never fabricate specs, prices or stock.</strong> Numbers come from the manufacturers and retailers and are dated; where something is approximate, we mark it. We'd rather leave a field blank than invent it.</li>
        <li><strong>We read the community for signal, not content.</strong> Reddit and the forums tell us what buyers are actually struggling with. We use that to decide what to write — then we write it ourselves, from scratch. We never scrape and republish.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How this is funded</h2>
      <p>{site.disclosure} The link you click never changes our verdict, and it never changes your price. If a recommendation ever reads like it was bought, call it out — that's a failure of the whole project.</p>

      <h2>Five bays, one engine</h2>
      <p>{site.name} covers five simulation disciplines — <a href="/racing">racing</a>, <a href="/flight">flight</a>, <a href="/space">space</a>, <a href="/marine">marine</a> and <a href="/golf">golf</a>. The hard part — the compatibility engine, the honest rating framework, the schema that makes our answers citable — is shared across all of them. Racing is the flagship and the proving ground; the rest follow the same playbook.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="band" style="margin-top:40px">
      <div>
        <span class="lbl lbl-accent">// Start here</span>
        <h3>Build a rig, the right way</h3>
        <p>The Rig Configurator is the fastest way to see how the honest-broker approach works in practice.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/racing/configurator">Open the configurator ▸</a>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
